YOUNG BROS., LTD., v. Mildred Winifred GILKES. No. 8638. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. Feb. 28, 1938. ■ Frank E. Thompson, of Honolulu, T. H., and John H. Black and James M. Wallace, both of San Francisco, Cal., for appellant. E. J. Botts and Fred Patterson, both of Honolulu, T. H., and Herbert Chamberlin, of San Francisco, Cal., for appellee.

Before WILBUR, GARRECHT, and DENMAN, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for respective parties, ordered appeal herein dismissed, that a decree of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and the mandate of this court herein issue forthwith,
